bers (percentages). ALP, alkaline phosphatase; CCI, Charlson comorbidity index; BP, blood pressure; AST,", "bbox": [45.5, 654.1, 720.1, 665.7]}, {"text": "aspartate aminotransferase; ALT, alanine aminotransferase; PTH, parathyroid hormone; TC, total cholesterol; hsCRP, high sensitivity C-Reactive Protein;", "bbox": [45.5, 669.3, 723.1, 680.9]}, {"text": "SGA, Subjective Global Assessment.", "bbox": [45.5, 684.5, 210.1, 696.1]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0157361.t001", "bbox": [45.5, 707.3, 186.2, 718.6]}, {"text": "peritonitis was the most common causes of infection-related deaths (43% of infection-related", "bbox": [252.5, 736.8, 716.4, 750.8]}, {"text": "death). Death from PD-related peritonitis was more likely in the higher tertiles of serum ALP", "bbox": [252.5, 753.3, 716.6, 767.2]}, {"text": "levels (p = 0.021). A Kaplan-Meier plot showed that infection-related mortality rate was signifi-", "bbox": [252.5, 769.7, 727.2, 783.6]}, {"text": "cantly increased in patients with the higher tertiles of serum ALP levels (P = 0.007, log-rank", "bbox": [252.5, 786.1, 708.6, 800.0]}, {"text": "test) (Fig 1A). Table 4 shows the results of univariate and multivariate Cox regression analysis", "bbox": [252.5, 802.5, 720.1, 816.4]}, {"text": "for infection-related mortality. In the crude model, the hazard ratio (HR) of infection-related", "bbox": [252.5, 818.9, 715.7, 832.9]}, {"text": "mortality of patients in tertile 2 of serum ALP levels was 2.46 (95% CI, 1.32–4.60, P = 0.005)", "bbox": [252.5, 835.3, 710.2, 849.3]}, {"text": "and HR of tertile 3 was 2.42 (95% CI, 1.29–4.56, P = 0.006) using tertile 1 as the reference cate-", "bbox": [252.5, 851.7, 723.2, 865.6]}, {"text": "gory. In multivariate Cox regression analysis, tertile 3 had a significantly independent higher", "bbox": [252.5, 868.2, 713.4, 882.1]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | DOI:10.1371/journal.pone.0157361 June 16, 2016 5 / 11", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}